 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udigrenkaellise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DigrenKaellise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 4:41:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14909.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Highjacking Thread Proposal...Opinions?</span><hr size=1> A lot of message boards don't have this problem because they allow thread branching.  The linear nature of EZBoard threads doesn't match the way humans really think; a given message may invoke different responses from each viewer, and each viewer of each response had his own opinion on that response, etc.<br>
<br>
When a branched thread is finished, it is often possible to identify the &quot;main&quot; branch of the thread.  However, while a given thread is under development, attempts to steer the thread will likely only cause frustration among those who disagree with the preferred branch.<br>
<br>
I could see the same problems if you were to, say, delete any replies that are not a direct reply to one of the last five messages on a thread.  This would eliminate random posts from people who only read the first post and skipped the next three pages of replies.  It would also keep threads more &quot;on topic&quot; as that topic shifts and refines.  But it would also prevent discussion on the points brought up by the that poster.<br>
<br>
In summary, the answer is: switch to a message board that allows thread branching; don't delete posts.<br>
<br>
Once threads can branch, you could always consider moderating or marking off-topic threads, trolls, flames, etc., as such, in the same way that (for example) slashdot does.<br>
<br>
Digren<br>
<br>
(Is my example of people not reading a whole thread before they reply off topic to this thread?  If someone replied specifically to that paragraph, would their reply be off topic?  Is mentioning branched threads as a solution to hijack threads off topic?  It isn't to me, but I'm not the moderator.)<br>
<br>
If you want to delete anything, delete posts by people who make horrible grammatical and spelling mistakes, then don't go back and edit their posts to fix them. ;P <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udigrenkaellise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DigrenKaellise</A> at: 3/18/02 4:45:39 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath>Paladins of Norrath</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral>General</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon">Paladins of Norrath Homepage</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  